704844f-a.text:
Henry Strect, north from Joralemon Street. The second car is at Hunt's Alley. In the distance on the right, is the Church of the Pilgrim's. The 4 1/2 story building at the right, was Hunt's Mansion built in 1868, of
Brownstone and Brick.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

226-230 Henry Street, west side, north from Joralemon Street.
The corner building is 113 Joralemon Street.

704845f-b.text:
Henry Street, north from Joralemon Street. View No. 1 shows the east side, and No. 2 the west side of Henry Street. While views Nos. 1 to 3 show the Church of the Pilgrims at Henry and Remsen Street.
August 10, 1935.
Views 2 & 3: April 5, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
